cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D data and scene understanding tasks. It also proposes a new convolutional neural network architecture for point cloud data. 

It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes an efficient end-to-end permutation invariant convolution for point cloud deep learning. 

Additionally, it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a new convolution operator named ShellConv. 

Finally, it may belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with 3D data and scene understanding tasks.
